Subject: Navier-Stokes Anti-Blowup Gate Matrix 001

Description: First populated matrix comparing candidate formal meanings of surface tension, resonance anchors, and phase correction against Navier-Stokes anti-blowup proof requirements.

& [MatrixFrame] is the comparison setup
  + [tool] is C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\platform\seven_math_problems\proof_inquiry\Navier_Stokes_Anti_Blowup_Gate_Matrix.sop
  + [source_shape] is surface tension and phase correction prevent turbulence from concentrating into singularity
  + [formal_target] is a bounded quantity or structure strong enough to satisfy a known continuation or regularity criterion
  + [proof_status] is inquiry_candidate_not_proof

& [SourceSet] is research evidence
  + [source_001] is Clay Mathematics Institute Navier-Stokes problem statement by Charles Fefferman
    = url: https://www.claymath.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/navierstokes.pdf
    = evidence: the problem asks for existence and smoothness or breakdown for 3D Navier-Stokes under specified smooth initial data
  + [source_002] is Tao "Why global regularity for Navier-Stokes is hard"
    = url: https://terrytao.wordpress.com/2007/03/18/why-global-regularity-for-navier-stokes-is-hard/
    = evidence: global regularity needs control stronger than the basic energy inequality because nonlinear energy transfer can concentrate at small scales
  + [source_003] is Beale-Kato-Majda criterion discussion
    = url: https://terrytao.wordpress.com/tag/beale-kato-majda-criterion/
    = evidence: smooth solutions continue unless a vorticity/gradient-type integral criterion blows up
  + [source_004] is Chan and Vasseur log-improved Prodi-Serrin criterion
    = url: https://web.ma.utexas.edu/users/vasseur/documents/preprints/summer2006.pdf
    = evidence: regularity follows from near-critical integrability control beyond basic energy bounds
  + [source_005] is Evan Miller strain equation thesis
    = url: https://www.math.toronto.edu/mccann/papers/MillerPhD19.pdf
    = evidence: strain and enstrophy growth identities expose geometric/nonlinear mechanisms relevant to concentration and regularity

& [Candidate_001_EnergyInequality] is a matrix row
  + [candidate_control] is energy inequality and viscosity dissipation
  + [controlled_quantity] is L2 kinetic energy and integrated gradient energy
  + [regularity_criterion_contact] is weak solution existence and energy dissipation, not full smooth continuation
  + [scaling_status] is subcritical_or_too_weak_for_3D_regularization
  + [anti_concentration_job] is limits total energy but does not prevent critical small-scale concentration
  + [known_boundary] is known_estimate_not_solution
  + [symbolic_fit] is error diffusion
  + [next_question] is what stronger quantity upgrades dissipation into regularity control

& [Candidate_002_EnstrophyVorticityControl] is a matrix row
  + [candidate_control] is enstrophy or vorticity norm control
  + [controlled_quantity] is L2 or Linfinity-type vorticity/gradient information
  + [regularity_criterion_contact] is BKM-style or continuation criteria involving vorticity/gradient blowup
  + [scaling_status] is closer_to_blowup_threshold_but_hard_to_bound
  + [anti_concentration_job] is directly targets vortex stretching and gradient concentration
  + [known_boundary] is criterion_known_boundedness_open
  + [symbolic_fit] is resonance anchor as bounded vorticity threshold
  + [next_question] is what mechanism could bound vortex stretching without assuming regularity

& [Candidate_003_ProdiSerrinCriticalNorm] is a matrix row
  + [candidate_control] is Prodi-Serrin or Ladyzhenskaya critical integrability
  + [controlled_quantity] is scale-critical velocity norm
  + [regularity_criterion_contact] is regularity if critical or near-critical spacetime norm remains finite
  + [scaling_status] is critical
  + [anti_concentration_job] is rules out scale-invariant concentration
  + [known_boundary] is criterion_known_boundedness_open
  + [symbolic_fit] is surface tension as critical norm containment
  + [next_question] is can the source approach suggest why critical norm should stay bounded

